Popular Nigerian journalist and blogger, Kemi Olunloyo has taken to her social media space to revealed she’s was involved in an accident.


The Investigative journalist confirmed that the accident happens this Saturday evening on the Lekki Epe express way.


According to Kemi Olunloyo, it was a pedestrian accident while adding she has driven a car in Nigeria as she uses the public transport system.
He tweet read: “At 7:30pm tonight I was involved in a pedestrian accident. It caused me a painful foot injury on the same foot I had surgery in July 2020. My blood pressure is low and fluctuating. I’ve never had a car in  use public transportation. I will be on medical leave indefinitely. ”










While narrating the extent of the injury she sustained from the accident, Kemi Olunloyo added that she will be away from the social media for while due to health reasons.She added:” This happened on Lekki Epe Expressway 4/30/22. I am in terrible pain and on painkillers now. Say a prayer for me. I will see you again soon. My phone is switched off as I cannot take calls at this time. Kemi Olunloyo Pharm.D”














